<subSubSection id="C37F6544FF8EFFBEDBA4FAC52F19973D" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA36CFFF8EFFBEDBA4FAC52F19973D" blockId="10.[151,1437,1301,1967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8EFFBEDBA4FAC52F4D9455" bold="true" box="[151,279,1301,1327]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length of male 
<quantity id="4C9D9B2AFF8EFFBEDAE8FAC52C609455" box="[475,570,1301,1327]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. Ground color stramineous infused with brown; anteclypeus and abdominal terga brown; crown spots, mesonotal triangles, and mesosternum dark brown; forewing with red longitudinal streak in clavus and another along vein Cu in basal half. Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4AFF8EFFBED8FCFAB52A719405" box="[975,1067,1381,1407]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[151,255,1451,1475]" captionTargetBox="[245,1323,197,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[244,1342,194,1427]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. New North American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, J, M, O, R, U, X), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, K, N, P, S, V, Y, AA) and posterior (C, F, I, L, Q, T, W, Z) views. A–C, N. antlera; D–F, N. chiapensis; G–I, N. hondurensis; J–L, N. mandibulata; M–N, N. obsoleta; O–Q, N. potosiensis; R–T, N. sonorensis; U–W, N. veracruzensis; X–Z, N. zapatai; AA, N. sordida." pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 3U</figureCitation>
) with dorsal appendage arising near apex, very slender, straight, not reaching distal margin; ventral appendage short, relatively broad, extended dorsomesad then curved dorsolaterad; lobe between appendages narrowly rounded, well sclerotized except near margin. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4AFF8EFFBED93AFA0D2CCD948D" box="[521,663,1501,1527]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[151,255,1451,1475]" captionTargetBox="[245,1323,197,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[244,1342,194,1427]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. New North American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, J, M, O, R, U, X), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, K, N, P, S, V, Y, AA) and posterior (C, F, I, L, Q, T, W, Z) views. A–C, N. antlera; D–F, N. chiapensis; G–I, N. hondurensis; J–L, N. mandibulata; M–N, N. obsoleta; O–Q, N. potosiensis; R–T, N. sonorensis; U–W, N. veracruzensis; X–Z, N. zapatai; AA, N. sordida." pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Figs. 3V, W</figureCitation>
) with shaft narrowly J-shaped, apex compressed, falcate in lateral view; distal processes arising distad of gonopore, sinuately curved posteroventrad, crossing each other medially near apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
