<paragraph id="8BDA36CFFF8EFFBEDBF5F9752F5E96D5" blockId="10.[151,1437,1301,1967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8EFFBEDBF5F9752F4997C5" bold="true" box="[198,275,1701,1727]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Notes.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54DE886DFF8EFFBEDA6BF9752FD097C5" box="[344,394,1701,1727]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
series was collected by vacuuming and sweeping low-growing sand dune vegetation along the Gulf Coast of 
<collectingRegion id="49A1F82DFF8EFFBEDAFBF91D2C69979D" box="[456,563,1741,1767]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F372765FFF8EFFBED977F91D2CF8979D" box="[580,674,1741,1767]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. The male genitalia of this species resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4CFF8EFFBEDE0CF91D2EAE9675" authority="Beamer" authorityName="Beamer. Beamer" authorityYear="1934" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balli">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8EFFBEDE0CF91D2BC6979C" box="[1343,1436,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">N. balli</emphasis>
Beamer
</taxonomicName>
, but the dorsal pygofer appendage is much more slender and elongate, the ventral appendage is longer, and the aedeagal shaft is much longer and nearly straight through most of its length. The coloration of the new species is also distinctive. The forewing of 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4CFF8EFFBED831F8952D9D9624" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2007" box="[770,967,1861,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veracruzensis">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8EFFBED831F8952D9D9624" box="[770,967,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">N. veracruzensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has reddish streaks only along vein Cu and in the clavus; 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4CFF8EFFBEDA58F8BD2F9996FC" authorityName="Beamer. Beamer" authorityYear="1934" box="[363,451,1901,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balli">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8EFFBEDA58F8BD2F9996FC" box="[363,451,1901,1926]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">N. balli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has more extensive areas of reddish pigment covering nearly the entire basal half of the wing.
</paragraph>
